  <prompt>
    Filed 2026-05-26 as a Phase 6 build-hygiene task after pre-existing compile errors in
    `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` were repeatedly flagged by R4 sub-agents (050, 053, 054).
    7 compile errors in 3 test files block `dotnet test` from running end-to-end, which means
    R4's BFF tests (PUT/PATCH/ETag boundary tests, attachment cap tests, modifiedOn wire-shape
    tests) cannot run as part of CI verification. Operator approved adding to R4 scope (2026-05-26).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    .NET 8 test-infrastructure engineer. The errors are likely stale fixtures, type drift, or
    missing dependencies in the test project — NOT design problems with the production handlers.
    Fix in test files only.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` completes with 0 errors. `dotnet test` runs the
    full test suite end-to-end. R4-added tests (PUT/PATCH/ETag, A-4 attachments, B-4 ModifiedOn
    wire shape) execute alongside existing tests. No production code modified.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Test files reporting compile errors (per R4 sub-agent reports):
      1. `AppOnlyDocumentAnalysisJobHandler` test file
      2. `EmbeddingMigrationService` test file
      3. `EmailAnalysisJobHandler` test file

      Cause is unknown until investigated — likely candidates: (a) stale fixture types drift from
      production refactors landed without test updates; (b) missing NuGet package after a dep cleanup;
      (c) implicit using namespaces stripped; (d) production handler API changed without test sync.

      Pre-existing baseline. Verified on master by R4 sub-agents (stash + retest).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Jobs/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Communication/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">No production code modification. Fix in test files (or test helper files like fixtures, builders, mocks) only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If a production class genuinely cannot be tested due to a real design issue, ESCALATE per CLAUDE.md §6 — do NOT modify production code to "make tests pass".</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">If a handler test touches AI-internal types, route through `PublicContracts/` facade where possible (per refined ADR-013, F-2 audit).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If a test is genuinely obsolete (e.g., tests a handler that no longer exists), DELETE it cleanly with a comment citing the original handler removal commit. Do NOT leave broken tests in the suite.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/CLAUDE.md</file>
