    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Reproduce">Run `dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` and capture all 7 compile errors. Document file + line + diagnostic ID.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Diagnose each">For each error, identify root cause: (a) type drift from production refactor, (b) missing dep, (c) namespace import issue, (d) genuine API change.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Categorize">Bin each error into: FIXABLE-IN-TEST, FIXABLE-VIA-FIXTURE-UPDATE, DELETE-OBSOLETE-TEST, or ESCALATE.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Apply test fixes">For each FIXABLE error: update the test file or fixture. Do NOT modify production code.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Handle obsolete tests">For DELETE-OBSOLETE-TEST errors: delete the test (or test method) with a brief comment citing the obsolescence reason + the production commit that removed the handler.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify build">`dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` → 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify test run">`dotnet test` runs end-to-end. Capture: total tests, passed, failed. Report failures (likely some existing test failures will surface, but they're separate from this task).</step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify R4 tests now run">Confirm R4-added tests are now in the test run output: (a) PUT/PATCH/ETag boundary tests (task 054); (b) attachment cap boundary tests (task 050 ChatEndpointsAttachmentsTests); (c) ModifiedOn wire-shape tests (task 053 WorkspaceLayoutEndpointTests).</step>
    <step order="9" name="Document">Write `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/test-infra-bff-handler-fix-2026-05-26.md` with the 7-error catalog, fixes applied, deletions made, and current `dotnet test` baseline.</step>
    <step order="10" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Change task 069 status to ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="11" name="Escalate (if applicable)">If any error required production-code change, ESCALATE before applying.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Inspect test files + fixtures + production handlers (read-only)</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Fix test files</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Run dotnet build + dotnet test</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Cross-reference handler usage</tool>
  </tools>

