    <criterion testable="true">R4-added BFF tests (050 attachments, 053 ModifiedOn, 054 PUT+ETag) appear in the test run output.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No production code modified in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` (verified via `git diff src/server/api/`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Memo at `notes/test-infra-bff-handler-fix-2026-05-26.md` catalogs all 7 errors + fixes/deletions.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Likely root causes (sorted by probability based on sub-agent reports):
    1. Type drift from R3+ production handler refactors that didn't update tests
    2. Missing `using` directives after a namespace reorganization
    3. NuGet package removal that orphaned test-only dependencies
    4. Production handler signature change (would surface as method-not-found errors)

    Do NOT pursue (out of scope, separate task):
    - Adding test coverage where none exists
    - Improving test quality / refactoring test patterns
    - Migrating to a different test framework

    Narrow to: get the build green + the suite running. Defer test quality improvements.
  </notes>

